2007-08-16  Francis Brosnan Blázquez  <francis@aspl.es>

	libvortex: * [fix] Fixed and integrated close in transit feature (test 09). Fixed some memory   leaks introduced by the new channel creation error API.

2007-08-15  Francis Brosnan Blázquez  <francis@aspl.es>

	libvortex: * [fix] Removed some checks not required at the second level frame received   dispatch function.

2007-08-15  Francis Brosnan Blázquez  <francis@aspl.es>

	libvortex: * [fix] Finished initial support for the cross close in transit. Now   the library support accepting an incoming close requested while a   reply for an outstanding close requested is waited, handling the   case as an implicit close. Added initial regression test but more   checks must be done.
	* [new] Added a new function to check the reference counting for a
	  channel. API added:

	   - vortex_channel_ref_count

2007-08-15  Francis Brosnan Blázquez  <francis@aspl.es>

	libvortex: * [new] Added two new macros that allows to register where the call to   vortex_cond_wait and vortex_cond_timedwait were produced. API added:
	    - VORTEX_COND_WAIT
	    - VORTEX_COND_TIMEDWAIT

	* [new] Added two new functions to implement a second level log (debug,
	  warning and error). Updated previous first level API to update its
	  status if a call to vortex_log_enable is done more times. Updating the
	  library to not drop message content if the second level is not activated.
	  API added:

	    - vortex_log2_is_enabled
	    - vortex_log2_enable

	* [new] Implemented initial code to support close in transit (BEEP peers
	  sending close messages at the same time). The code tries to detect that
	  situation and perform an implicit close. Added an initial regression test
	  to check this feature.

2007-08-14  Francis Brosnan Blázquez  <francis@aspl.es>

	libaxl: * [fix] More regression tests on axl list storing integers..

	libaxl: * [fix] Fixed axl_list_remove to use an internal linear search to ensure   it doesn't skip any element to be removed due to axlListEqual hints.   Updated regression test to check this.

	libaxl: * [fix] Fixed bug inside axl_list_equal_int which was causing to   not properly handle integer lists. Updated regression test to check   this in future releases.

	libvortex: * [new] Added new function to produce a digest configuring the amount of   data to be taken from the input. API added:
	    - vortex_tls_get_digest_sized

2007-08-13  Francis Brosnan Blázquez  <francis@aspl.es>

