2007-03-15  Francis Brosnan Blázquez  <francis@aspl.es>

	libvortex: * [fix] commiting changes to remove GList references at the vortex channel module.

	vortex-client: * [fix] Fixed wrong handler provided to the connection status command.

	libvortex: * [fix] Simplified automatic frame joining handling at the vortex reader/vortex channel   module, updating vortex_channel_set_previous_frame/get_previous_frame/have_previous_frame   to use a simple implementation based in an unique pending frame to be joined rather   than a list.
	* [fix] Fixed a bug at the vortex_hash_replace function, which was causing to not configure
	  the key and data destroy function causing memory leaks.

2007-03-15  Francis Brosnan Blázquez  <francis@aspl.es>

	libvortex: * [fix] Replaced all calls to g_async_queue_push with QUEUE_PUSH, implementing   addintionall checks that are reported at the place they could fail.
	* [fix] Fixed wrong reply handling for the TLS activation, using the sync mode.
	  Seems it doesn't work under heavy load circumstances.

	* [fix] Making vortex sequencer to check the queue before operating with it.
	  Some race conditions under heavy load could cause to access to a null reference
	  queue.

2007-03-15  Francis Brosnan Blázquez  <francis@aspl.es>

	xml-rpc-gen: * [new] General update to the source code generation model.   Now the tool will detect which files have changes according to   the source code created, allowing the user to skip those changes   or to introduce them.

2007-03-15  Francis Brosnan Blázquez  <francis@aspl.es>

	xml-rpc-gen: * [fix] Fixed marshalling error at the server side component source code generation,   causing to trying marshall an array as an struct. (Bug reported by Vicent AE Scott,   and pointed its solution).
	* [fix] Improved marshalling error reporting at the server side component produced
	  by the tool.

	* [fix] Updating exarg code.

2007-03-12  Francis Brosnan Blázquez  <francis@aspl.es>

	* [fix] Commiting last changes to validate turbulence main configuration   file.

	libaxl: * [fix] Making more verbose the dtd validation error found for undefined   nodes.

	* [new] Commiting initial files for the new BEEP server application.
